'''Yanagimoto Kofun Group''' (柳本古墳群, *Yanagimoto Kofungun*) is a group of early {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofun period|qq=}} Kofuns located in Yanagimoto-chō, {{ill|Tenri, Nara Prefecture|ja|天理市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenri, Nara Prefecture|qq=}}. Together with the {{ill|Yamato Kofun Group|ja|大和古墳群|1=Ōyamato Kofun Group|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Kofun Group|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamato Kofun Group|qq=}}, it is also referred to as the '''Yamato-Yanagimoto Kofun Group''' (大和・柳本古墳群). To the south lies the {{ill|Makimuku Kofun Cluster|lt=Makimuku Kofun Cluster|lt=Makimuku Kofun Group|ja|纏向古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Makimuku Kofun Group|qq=}}.
== Overview == This kofun group is situated on the southern ridges of hills, separated by a valley from the {{ill|Yamato Kofun Group|ja|大和古墳群|1=Ōyamato Kofun Group|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Kofun Group|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamato Kofun Group|qq=}}, and comprises two large kofun and several medium- and small-sized keyhole-shaped tumuli (前方後円墳). The main mound, {{ill|Andon-yama Kofun|ja|行燈山古墳|1=Andon-yama Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Andon-yama Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Andon-yama Kofun|qq=}}, is accompanied by three subordinate tumuli: {{ill|Yamato Tenjinyama Kofun|ja|大和天神山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Tenjinyama Kofun|qq=}}, {{ill|Andon-yama Kofun|ja|行燈山古墳|1=Andon-yama Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Andon-yama Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Andon-yama Kofun|qq=}} (120 meters), and {{ill|Andon-yama Kofun|ja|南アンド山古墳|Andon-yama Kofun=Andon-yama Kofun|lt=South Ando-yama Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Andon-yama Kofun|qq=}} (65 meters). To the south, another group centers on {{ill|Shibutani Mukoyama Kofun|ja|渋谷向山古墳|1=Shibutani Mukoyama Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibutani Mukoyama Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibutani Mukoyama Kofun|qq=}} and includes the {{ill|Kamiyama Kofun|ja|上ノ山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamiyama Kofun|qq=}} (125 meters) and {{ill|Shiurou Kofun|ja|シウロウ塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiurou Kofun|qq=}} (120 meters). To the west, tumuli such as {{ill|Yanagimoto Otsuka Kofun|ja|柳本大塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yanagimoto Otsuka Kofun|qq=}} (94 meters) are scattered.
The royal tombs following the Yamato-Yanagimoto Kofun Group shifted from the southeastern part of the Nara Basin to the northwest, forming the {{ill|Saki Tsurugamine Kofun Group|ja|佐紀盾列古墳群|1=Saki Tatenami Kofun group|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saki Tsurugamine Kofun Group|13=User:Immanuelle/Saki Tatenami Kofun group|qq=}} (western group). This shift is thought to reflect the relocation of royal power.
== Notable Kofun == [[File:Andonyama 001.jpg|thumb|230px|right|{{center|Andon-yama Kofun}}{{small|{{国土航空写真}}.}]]] [[File:CG S Mukaiyama Kofun 11 7p BW.jpg|thumb|230px|right|{{center|Shibutani Mukoyama Kofun}]]] [[File:Yodo River and Yamato River Basins.svg|300px|thumb|right|Location of the Yanagimoto Kofun Group and nearby kofun groups]]
